(272, 1, 1, 'When I survey the wondrous cross'),
(272, 1, 2, 'On which the Lord of glory died,'),
(272, 1, 3, 'My richest gain I count but loss,'),
(272, 1, 4, 'And pour contempt on all my pride.'),
(272, 2, 1, 'Far be the thought that I should boast,'),
(272, 2, 2, 'Save in the cross of Christ, my Lord;'),
(272, 2, 3, 'All the vain things that charm me most,'),
(272, 2, 4, 'I\'d sacrifice them at His word.'),
(272, 3, 1, 'There from His head, His hands, His feet,'),
(272, 3, 2, 'Sorrow and love flowed mingled down;'),
(272, 3, 3, 'Did e\'er such love and sorrow meet,'),
(272, 3, 4, 'Or thorns compose so rich a crown?'),
(272, 4, 1, 'Were the whole realm of nature mine,'),
(272, 4, 2, 'That were an off\'ring far too small;'),
(272, 4, 3, 'Love so amazing, so divine,'),
(272, 4, 4, 'Demands my soul, my life, my all!'),
(273, 1, 1, 'How wondrous a Saviour is God\'s blessed Son!'),
(273, 1, 2, 'How great and eternal the work He has done!'),
(273, 1, 3, 'God\'s glory maintained by His death on the tree,'),
(273, 1, 4, 'While mercy flows freely to you and to me.'),
(273, 2, 1, 'How free is the pardon His blood has procured!'),
(273, 2, 2, 'How blessed the welcome His Name has ensured'),
(273, 2, 3, 'To all who confess Him their Saviour and Lord -'),
(273, 2, 4, 'Now brought into favour, believing His word.'),
(273, 3, 1, 'On Calvary see Him who died in our stead,'),
(273, 3, 2, 'In glory behold Him exalted as Head;'),
(273, 3, 3, 'God\'s wrath He endured on Calvary\'s tree,'),
(273, 3, 4, 'By weakness and dying the Victor was He.'),
(273, 4, 1, 'To those who obey Him has God freely giv\'n'),
(273, 4, 2, 'The blest Holy Spirit as poured out from heav\'n;'),
(273, 4, 3, 'Who witnesses here to Christ\'s glory above:'),
(273, 4, 4, 'Receiving this blessing we live in God\'s love.'),
(274, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus, come,'),
(274, 1, 2, 'And take Thy rightful place'),
(274, 1, 3, 'As Son of man, of all the theme!'),
(274, 1, 4, 'Come, Lord, to reign o\'er all supreme,'),
(274, 1, 5, 'Lord Jesus, come!'),
(274, 2, 1, 'Lord Jesus, come!'),
(274, 2, 2, 'The Man of sorrows once,'),
(274, 2, 3, 'The Man of patience waiting now,'),
(274, 2, 4, 'The Man of joy, for ever, Thou:'),
(274, 2, 5, 'Come, Saviour, come!'),
(274, 3, 1, 'Lord Jesus, come!'),
(274, 3, 2, 'Let every knee bow down,'),
(274, 3, 3, 'And every tongue to Thee confess,'),
(274, 3, 4, 'The Lord of all come forth to bless:'),
(274, 3, 5, 'Lord Jesus, come!'),
(274, 4, 1, 'Spirit and bride'),
(274, 4, 2, 'With longing voice, say, Come!'),
(274, 4, 3, 'Yea, Lord, Thy word from that bright home'),
(274, 4, 4, 'Is, Surely, I will quickly come!'),
(274, 4, 5, 'E\'en so, Lord, come!'),
(275, 1, 1, 'All men have sinned and short of glory come;'),
(275, 1, 2, 'The Scripture saith, None righteous, no not one!'),
(275, 1, 3, 'No hope hath man, deceived and far from God,'),
(275, 1, 4, 'Guilty and lost, exposed to judgment\'s rod.'),
(275, 2, 1, 'One Mediator, Christ, of God and men,'),
(275, 2, 2, 'Who on the tree once died, and rose again:'),
(275, 2, 3, 'No other name but His can sinners save -'),
(275, 2, 4, 'Jesus, who rose triumphant o\'er the grave.'),
(275, 3, 1, 'Forgiveness now is preached through Him who died,'),
(275, 3, 2, 'The Lord of glory who was crucified.'),
(275, 3, 3, 'His finished work has met our every need;'),
(275, 3, 4, 'And brought us nigh to God as free indeed!'),
(275, 4, 1, 'Sealed by the Spirit till redemption\'s day,'),
(275, 4, 2, 'Sealed till the Bridegroom takes His bride away,'),
(275, 4, 3, 'We Christ await: He will not reign alone,'),
(275, 4, 4, 'But take the church, His bride, to share His throne.'),
(276, 1, 1, 'Have you not heard the joyful sound?'),
(276, 1, 2, 'Glad tidings through the world resound -'),
(276, 1, 3, 'Of pardon, peace, salvation free,'),
(276, 1, 4, 'God\'s blessed way of liberty.'),
(276, 1, 5, 'His word believe,'),
(276, 1, 6, 'His Son receive,'),
(276, 1, 7, 'Who died for such as we.'),
(276, 2, 1, 'Thy footsteps haste! the day draws near'),
(276, 2, 2, 'When careless souls shall quake and fear.'),
(276, 2, 3, 'Here is a refuge open wide,'),
(276, 2, 4, 'Salvation now in Him who died.'),
(276, 2, 5, 'His blood was shed;'),
(276, 2, 6, 'Raised from the dead,'),
(276, 2, 7, 'He now is glorified.'),
(276, 3, 1, 'O why not then in Christ confide?'),
(276, 3, 2, 'If works could save, would He have died?'),
(276, 3, 3, 'Now hearken to His blessed cry,'),
(276, 3, 4, '\"\'Tis finished!\" He is crowned on high.'),
(276, 3, 5, 'To Him now look'),
(276, 3, 6, 'Who judgment took,'),
(276, 3, 7, 'And on His work rely.'),
(276, 4, 1, 'Henceforth art thou for glory meet,'),
(276, 4, 2, 'By blood made nigh, in Christ complete;'),
(276, 4, 3, 'And thus to walk before His face,'),
(276, 4, 4, 'Blessed in the riches of His grace;'),
(276, 4, 5, 'To serve Him here'),
(276, 4, 6, 'With godly fear,'),
(276, 4, 7, 'A holy heav\'nly race.'),
(277, 1, 1, 'God and Father, we adore Thee,'),
(277, 1, 2, 'Now revealed in Christ the Son,'),
(277, 1, 3, 'Joying in Thy holy presence'),
(277, 1, 4, 'Through the work that He has done.'),
(277, 2, 1, 'Filled with praise we bow before Thee;'),
(277, 2, 2, 'Thou art evermore the Same;'),
(277, 2, 3, 'With adoring hearts we bless Thee,'),
(277, 2, 4, 'Magnify Thy holy Name.'),
(277, 3, 1, 'Worship, honour, praise and glory,'),
(277, 3, 2, 'Would we render unto Thee;'),
(277, 3, 3, 'Heights unsearched and depths unfathomed'),
(277, 3, 4, 'In Thy wondrous love we see.'),
(277, 4, 1, 'All Thy glory shines transcendent'),
(277, 4, 2, 'In the person of the Son,'),
(277, 4, 3, 'Jesus Christ, Thy Well-beloved,'),
(277, 4, 4, 'Who redemption\'s glory won.'),
(277, 5, 1, 'By the Spirit we behold Him,'),
(277, 5, 2, 'Object of Thy heart\'s deep love;'),
(277, 5, 3, 'Boundless theme of adoration'),
(277, 5, 4, 'In that scene of joy above.'),
(277, 6, 1, 'In Thy grace Thou now hast brought us'),
(277, 6, 2, 'Sharers of Thy joy to be'),
(277, 6, 3, 'And to know the blessed secret'),
(277, 6, 4, 'Of His preciousness to Thee.'),
(278, 1, 1, 'Saviour, we long to follow Thee,'),
(278, 1, 2, 'Do Thou our hearts prepare'),
(278, 1, 3, 'To count all else, whate\'er it be,'),
(278, 1, 4, 'Unworthy of our care.'),
(278, 2, 1, 'We are not now our own, but Thine,'),
(278, 2, 2, 'The purchase of Thy blood,'),
(278, 2, 3, 'And made, by grace and love divine,'),
(278, 2, 4, 'The sons and heirs of God.'),
(278, 3, 1, 'Thy Spirit, too, the present seal'),
(278, 3, 2, 'Of all the Father\'s love,'),
(278, 3, 3, 'Dwells in us now and doth reveal'),
(278, 3, 4, 'The glorious rest above.'),
(278, 4, 1, 'Thy life is now beyond the grave;'),
(278, 4, 2, 'Our souls Thou hast set free;'),
(278, 4, 3, 'Life, strength and grace in thee we have,'),
(278, 4, 4, 'And we are one with Thee.'),
(278, 5, 1, 'O teach us so Thy power to know,'),
(278, 5, 2, 'As risen, Lord, with Thee,'),
(278, 5, 3, 'That we may own, while here below,'),
(278, 5, 4, 'Thyself our life to be.'),
(279, 1, 1, 'Jesus! the very thought of Thee'),
(279, 1, 2, 'With sweetness fills the breast;'),
(279, 1, 3, 'But sweeter far Thy face to see'),
(279, 1, 4, 'And in Thy presence rest.'),
(279, 2, 1, 'No voice can sing, no heart can frame,'),
(279, 2, 2, 'Nor can the memory find'),
(279, 2, 3, 'A sweeter sound than Thy blest Name,'),
(279, 2, 4, 'O Saviour of mankind!'),
(279, 3, 1, 'O hope of every contrite heart,'),
(279, 3, 2, 'O joy of all the meek,'),
(279, 3, 3, 'To those who ask how kind Thou art,'),
(279, 3, 4, 'How good to those who seek!'),
(279, 4, 1, 'But what to those who find? Ah! this'),
(279, 4, 2, 'Nor tongue nor pen can show;'),
(279, 4, 3, 'The love of Jesus, what it is,'),
(279, 4, 4, 'None but His loved ones know.'),
(279, 5, 1, 'Jesus! our present joy art Thou,'),
(279, 5, 2, 'As Thou our prize wilt be;'),
(279, 5, 3, 'In Thee be all our glory now,'),
(279, 5, 4, 'As through eternity.'),
(280, 1, 1, 'Lord Jesus Christ, to thee a song we raise,'),
(280, 1, 2, 'Both heart and voice uniting in Thy praise.'),
(280, 1, 3, 'Thine excellence and glory fill our sight;'),
(280, 1, 4, 'To Thee be honour, majesty and might!'),
(280, 2, 1, 'What love from Thee to Thine assembly flows!'),
(280, 2, 2, 'What nearness sweet and full she ever knows!'),
(280, 2, 3, 'Her joy complete in knowing that Thy heart'),
(280, 2, 4, 'Is satisfied in Thy blest counterpart.'),
(280, 3, 1, 'Bone of Thy bones, flesh of Thy flesh, the bride'),
(280, 3, 2, 'Can take her place in glory at Thy side,'),
(280, 3, 3, 'In love\'s complacency - no distance known -'),
(280, 3, 4, 'To her Thou\'rt Head o\'er all things, glorious One!'),
(281, 1, 1, 'Jesus, my Saviour! Thou art mine,'),
(281, 1, 2, 'The Father\'s gift of love divine;'),
(281, 1, 3, 'What Thou hast done, and what Thou art,'),
(281, 1, 4, 'Are now the portion of my heart.'),
(281, 2, 1, 'Poor, feeble, failing, as I am,'),
(281, 2, 2, 'I now can glory in Thy Name;'),
(281, 2, 3, 'Now cleansed by thy most precious blood,'),
(281, 2, 4, 'And counted righteous by Thy God.'),
(281, 3, 1, 'Thy fulness, Lord, is now for me,'),
(281, 3, 2, 'All my fresh springs are hid in Thee;'),
(281, 3, 3, 'In Thee I live; while I confess'),
(281, 3, 4, 'I nothing am, yet all possess.'),
(281, 4, 1, 'O Saviour, teach me to abide'),
(281, 4, 2, 'Close sheltered at Thy trusted side,'),
(281, 4, 3, 'Each hour receiving grace on grace,'),
(281, 4, 4, 'Until I see Thee face to face.'),
(282, 1, 1, 'God gave His Son for sinners;'),
(282, 1, 2, 'Christ died upon the tree;'),
(282, 1, 3, 'My soul is filled with wonder'),
(282, 1, 4, 'As now His grace I see!'),
(282, 1, 5, 'Shout, shout aloud, ye saved ones,'),
(282, 1, 6, 'And spread abroad His fame!'),
(282, 1, 7, 'Praise ye the glorious Saviour,'),
(282, 1, 8, 'Give honour to His Name.'),
(282, 2, 1, 'Give unto Him the glory,'),
(282, 2, 2, 'Who, in His wondrous love,'),
(282, 2, 3, 'Brought us so great salvation'),
(282, 2, 4, 'From yon high courts above.'),
(282, 2, 5, 'Jesus our Lord has triumphed;'),
(282, 2, 6, 'Salvation free is mine.'),
(282, 2, 7, 'Let every soul adore Him,'),
(282, 2, 8, 'Saved by His grace divine.'),
(282, 3, 1, 'Washed in His blood most precious,'),
(282, 3, 2, 'Lift up your hearts in praise'),
(282, 3, 3, 'Now, all ye heirs of glory,'),
(282, 3, 4, 'And to eternal days.'),
(282, 3, 5, 'Shout, shout aloud, ye saved ones,'),
(282, 3, 6, 'And spread abroad His fame!'),
(282, 3, 7, 'Praise ye the glorious Saviour,'),
(282, 3, 8, 'Give honour to His Name.'),
(283, 1, 1, 'As in Thy presence, Lord, our spirits free,'),
(283, 1, 2, 'Thy brethren now respond with joy to Thee;'),
(283, 1, 3, 'We answer to Thy call in kinship\'s place,'),
(283, 1, 4, 'And near to Thee we know Thine own embrace.'),
(283, 2, 1, '\"My brethren\" - Lord, these precious words are Thine.'),
(283, 2, 2, 'What glorious thoughts now flow in light divine,'),
(283, 2, 3, 'As, in this nearness, yielding Thee Thy joy,'),
(283, 2, 4, 'We raise our song to Thee - our blest employ!');
INSERT INTO `hymn_line` (`hymn_no`, `vers_no`, `line_no`, `line_text`) VALUES
(283, 3, 1, 'We praise Thee, blessed Lord; our souls would move'),
