(289, 2, 3, 'Thy willing servants, let us wear'),
(289, 2, 4, 'The seal of love for ever there.'),
(289, 3, 1, 'How blest are they who still abide'),
(289, 3, 2, 'Close sheltered by Thy watchful side,'),
(289, 3, 3, 'Who life and strength from Thee receive,'),
(289, 3, 4, 'And with Thee move, and in Thee live!'),
(289, 4, 1, 'Ah, Lord, enlarge our scanty thought,'),
