(394, 3, 2, 'For the sins He knew so well;'),
(394, 3, 3, 'On the cross Himself He offered,'),
(394, 3, 4, 'That Thou mightest with Him dwell.'),
(394, 4, 1, 'Come to Him! His heart so tender,'),
(394, 4, 2, 'And His grace would Thee compel;'),
(394, 4, 3, 'Yield to Him in full surrender,'),
(394, 4, 4, 'And with Him for ever dwell!'),
(394, 5, 1, 'Living water He would give thee;'),
(394, 5, 2, 'Satisfied, thy praise shall swell'),
(394, 5, 3, 'To the God who gives so freely,'),
(394, 5, 4, 'Who would have thee with Him dwell.'),
(394, 6, 1, 'Ask then for the Spirit Holy -'),
(394, 6, 2, 'He who is the springing well,'),
(394, 6, 3, 'Power for life and joy within thee -'),
(394, 6, 4, 'He would come with thee to dwell.'),
(395, 1, 1, 'Great Captain of salvation,'),
(395, 1, 2, 'Now crowned with highest glory,'),
(395, 1, 3, 'We joyful raise our songs of praise,'),
(395, 1, 4, 'And lowly bow before Thee.'),
(395, 1, 5, 'We worship and adore Thee,'),
(395, 1, 6, 'Each heart and tongue confessing,'),
(395, 1, 7, 'To Thee once slain - worthy to reign -'),
(395, 1, 8, 'Be honour, power and blessing!'),
(395, 2, 1, 'Thou hast the cross endured'),
(395, 2, 2, 'In love beyond all measure,'),
(395, 2, 3, 'The curse, the grave, Thy saints to save,'),
(395, 2, 4, 'And have us as Thy treasure.'),
(395, 2, 5, 'We see Thee as the Victim,'),
(395, 2, 6, 'Our sins and sorrows bearing,'),
(395, 2, 7, 'The Lamb once slain, alive again,'),
(395, 2, 8, 'The crown of glory wearing.'),
(395, 3, 1, 'Head of the vast creation,'),
(395, 3, 2, 'To God\'s right hand ascended:'),
(395, 3, 3, 'Thy saints rejoice with heart and voice,'),
(395, 3, 4, 'Before Thy feet low bended.'),
(395, 3, 5, 'We own Thee, Lord, exulting'),
(395, 3, 6, 'In all Thy joy and glory,'),
(395, 3, 7, 'And long to be on high with Thee'),
(395, 3, 8, 'Where all shall bow before Thee.'),
(396, 1, 1, 'Rock of Ages! cleft for me,'),
(396, 1, 2, 'Let me hide myself in Thee;'),
(396, 1, 3, 'Let the water and the blood,'),
(396, 1, 4, 'From Thy riven side which flowed,'),
(396, 1, 5, 'Be of sin the double cure,'),
(396, 1, 6, 'Cleansing from its guilt and power.'),
(396, 2, 1, 'Not the labour of my hands'),
(396, 2, 2, 'Could fulfil the law\'s demands;'),
(396, 2, 3, 'Could my zeal no respite know,'),
(396, 2, 4, 'Could my tears for ever flow,'),
(396, 2, 5, 'Nought for sins could e\'er atone'),
(396, 2, 6, 'But Thy blood, and Thine alone.'),
(396, 3, 1, 'Nothing in my hand I bring,'),
(396, 3, 2, 'Simply to Thyself I cling;'),
(396, 3, 3, 'Naked, come to Thee for dress;'),
(396, 3, 4, 'Helpless, look to Thee for grace;'),
(396, 3, 5, 'Foul, I to the fountain fly;'),
(396, 3, 6, 'Wash me, Saviour, or I die.'),
(396, 4, 1, 'Found by Thee before I sought,'),
(396, 4, 2, 'Unto Thee in mercy brought;'),
(396, 4, 3, 'I have Thee for righteousness,'),
(396, 4, 4, 'From Thy fulness grace on grace;'),
(396, 4, 5, 'Thou hast washed me in Thy blood,'),
