(397, 1, 1, 'Jesus, Thy head, once crowned with thorns,'),
(397, 1, 2, 'Is crowned with glory now;'),
(397, 1, 3, 'Heav\'n\'s royal diadem adorns'),
(397, 1, 4, 'The mighty Victor\'s brow.'),
(397, 2, 1, 'Thou glorious light of courts above,'),
(397, 2, 2, 'Joy of the saints below,'),
(397, 2, 3, 'To us still manifest Thy love,'),
(397, 2, 4, 'That we its depths may know.'),
(397, 3, 1, 'To us Thy cross with all its shame,'),
(397, 3, 2, 'With all its grace, be giv\'n;'),
(397, 3, 3, 'Though earth disowns Thy lowly Name,'),
(397, 3, 4, 'God honours it in heav\'n.'),
(397, 4, 1, 'Who suffer with Thee, Lord, below,'),
(397, 4, 2, 'Shall reign with thee above;'),
(397, 4, 3, 'Then let it be our joy to know'),
(397, 4, 4, 'This way of peace and love.'),
(397, 5, 1, 'To us Thy cross is life and health,'),
(397, 5, 2, '\'Twas shame and death to Thee;'),
(397, 5, 3, 'Our present glory, joy and wealth,'),
(397, 5, 4, 'Our everlasting stay.'),
(398, 1, 1, 'Thy death and resurrection, Lord,'),
(398, 1, 2, '(How faith rejoices in the word!)'),
(398, 1, 3, 'Have met the charge that on us lay,'),
(398, 1, 4, 'And taken all death\'s sting away.'),
(398, 2, 1, 'Soon all the saints who through Thee sleep,'),
(398, 2, 2, 'Th\'appointment in the air will keep,'),
(398, 2, 3, 'When, rising from Thy Father\'s throne,'),
(398, 2, 4, 'Thou comest forth to claim Thine own.'),
(398, 3, 1, 'Thy voice the realm of death shall burst,'),
(398, 3, 2, 'The dead in Christ arising first;'),
